name: True Crime Cases from Police Files

description: Following The System and Seven Miles a Second comes a 3-issue mini-series from the Vertigo Verite line of groundbreaking, provocative fiction and intense-life stories: Fifteen-year-old Simone Cundy hates her so-called life. Dreaming of escape from her insufferable family and her unbearable home town, she embarks upon a dangerous and hilarious quest for freedom in this black-humored tale of one young woman's rite of passage.
name: My Life As A Social Engineer

description: After a bizarre encounter with a blonde girl who bears an uncanny resemblance to her, Simone sports her own platinum wig and concocts an escape route out of her home town, following the mysterious Polly--who isn't all she's cracked up to be. But Simone finds that life as a blond has its drawbacks. Among them, a run-in with the police, and trouble with boys and an ancient burial gone awry. Kicking and screaming, Simone's finally forced to return to the abysmal confines of her dysfunctional family--where death, decay and disaster await her.
name: My Life As A Concerned Daughter

description: On the run and wanted for murder, Simone must shatter the illusions that make life in Bollockstown worth living in order to find out the truth. But will the truth destroy the girl...or the town?
name: My Life As A Nutter

description:
Bart Simpson's favorite TV terrors in their carnage-filled first issue! Scratchy the cat is down and out, having blown his fortune from "The Itchy & Scratchy Show." But the ever-abused feline has plans for landing on his feet -- he enters a million dollar around-the-world race. But when Itchy the mouse shows up at the starting line as well, the only possible outcome is gratuitous violence on a global scale! See the mayhem-minded mouse and the much-mangled cat go Around the World in 80 Pieces.

"Bart Simpson's Favorite Cartoon"

"1st issue! Carnage crammed collectors item!"
name: Around the World in 80 Pieces

description: A comics first! This issue is co-written by Dan Castellaneta, the voice of Homer Simpson! Bongo takes you on location for a behind-the-scenes look at the making of the new Itchy and Scratchy movie! Watch the twin terrors of television battle on-screen and off to bring their new artistic vision to life--and death! See the stars get wired! The production get mired! The director get fired! Hear all the inside dirt on Itchy and Scratchy and their off-camera escapades-- their backstabbing brawls--their creative feuds with the producer--the budget battles with the studio! It's sleazy! It's sordid! It's shocking! It's tabloid journalism at its finest and funniest!
name: The Itchy & Scratchy Movie II

description:
1. Labor Pains -- 2. When Bongos Collide crossover (part 1 : Part 2 is in Simpsons Comics #5)

"Part 1 of 'When Bongos Collide' crossover! With special guest star Bart Simpson!"

"Exclusive Skybox decoder card inside!"
name: When Bongos Collide Part 1

description: Zinnak and Yoof are two alien college students doing a project on superheroes. They develop a superhuman power package and a device to attract trouble. Incompetence sends the powers to Lou Martin, a shiftless lazy kid with no ambition. It was supposed to go to Lewis Martin, a philathropist and lawyer. Other heroes come forward, most more heroic then Lou but with flaws of their own.
name: What The Hell..?

description: Major Bummer gets a new costume! Well actually he just changes his shirt. Meanwhile, aliens, evil doers, and big guns are the order of the day as the origin of Dc’s slacker super hero concludes.
name: Term Paper Of The...Gods?

description: Louis Martin attempts to keep his life in check, or at best normal, fixing VCR's at the electronics store he works. He runs into Martin Lewis- the man designated to gain his powers- as well as the superhuman team he was set to side with. Yoof has in the meantime taken a collection of hoods plus their mugger to be given new super-powers to destroy the "heroes" as they watch from their ship.
name: Alone Against The Other Guys!

description: A Nazi Dinosaur attacks the town. The hero's allies step up to the job, managing to stalemate the homicidal creature. Other problem's seize Lou's attention.
name: No Matter

description: Milton Tweeleg decides he’s tired of getting kicked around by life. He gets dumped by his girlfriend, blows the job interview, and gets his face pushed in by a bully. Now he wants someone else to live his less than stellar life for a while. All in a day’s work for Major bummer.
name: Idle Worship

description: Move over McGyver, DC's got the new miracle-working gadgeteer on the block. Last issue, Milton Tweeleg took a metal detector, a small Eastern European car, and a disposable lighter and did the impossible, transforming Lou Martin into a respected celebrity (something the writer of this book hasn't been able to achieve yet!). This month, Milton's at it again. He's about to change Lou's life forever with nothing more than an axe! Plus, Nunzio shows us his shy side, and Francis discovers that Dorothy was right: "There's no place like home."
name: Only The Good Die Young
